    {
      "id": "52553ab49a4af08f7dd0c7515875a3d6fc65907d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-01-24 08:57:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, this patch doesn't address FID-on-OST in that sense. it's required to access legacy format with /O mapping. I'd like to land it in current form (with fixes, of course) to allow OFD landing required for LLNL. later (asap, i guess) we should address FID-on-OST to allow DNE. are you still against the approach?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "cd9dbaaa9ec228c33a42bfc8d846dcdba08d0b58",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-01-24 09:00:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nforgot to mention that even with FID-on-OST and some flag/type identifying OST objects we still need to use /O if this is IDIF ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "22f561239338b577efccf3c44fdbbfc2f7b475c8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-01-25 08:47:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm ok with landing this code without the FID-on-OST support as a preliminary step to getting OFD working on master. However, I'd like to make sure that the code that is landed is itself as clean as possible, since this is our one chance to get it right. If this code is landed with hacks and workarounds then it will likely remain that way for a long time, and I'd rather avoid this problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7397b6d5a617b0cb56d85dd337e7a2132876d315",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
